      <Paragraph/>
      <Paragraph>Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) Microsoft build engine (MSBuild) support provides a special .targets file, <Run FontWeight="Bold">Microsoft.WinFX.targets</Run>
, which combines the set of MSBuild tasks that are required to build a WPF MSBuild project.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph FontSize="22">Subhead    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph>When an MSBuild project is built, normally one or more MSBuild tasks are used during the build process. MSBuild provides the ability to create special files that contain multiple tasks for common scenarios. These files are known as target files, and have the <Run FontWeight="Bold">.targets</Run>
 extension.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph>WPF extends MSBuild with a set of additional, WPF -specific tasks, which are combined into a special .targets file, <Run FontWeight="Bold">Microsoft.WinFX.targets</Run>
.    
      </Paragraph>

